_:N3014306fb7404790b5d62f2c1a4ffad9 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Baroness Evans of Bowes Park was Lord Privy Seal and Leader of the House of Lords between 14 July 2016 and 6 September 2022.</p>\n\n<p>She previously served as a Baroness in Waiting from May 2015 until July 2016.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"education\">Education</h2>\n\n<p>She was educated at Henrietta Barnett School and at the University of Cambridge, where she studied social and political sciences.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"political-career\">Political career</h2>\n\n<p>Baroness Evans was made a life Peer in September 2014 and has previously served as Deputy Director of the Conservative Research Department.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"career-outside-politics\">Career outside politics</h2>\n\n<p>Baroness Evans was previously deputy director of Policy Exchange and the chief operating officer and director of the New Schools Network.</p>\n" .
